                     <interp inst="t18300916-266-person2192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and John Appleford; the witness told me a pair of trousers had been stolen - there is a mark on them; they were on the door-post.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-266-person2193">
                  THOMAS 
                  MOOR
               <interp inst="t18300916-266-person2193" type="surname" value="MOOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-266-person2193" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-266-person2193" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I took Ward; I saw Wheeler throw down the trousers - Ward was walking down Coppice-row; the witness said he was the man he saw at the door.</p>
               <p>Ward. I was going to Smithfield - I was never in his company at all.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183009160119"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-266-person2194">
